 Minister Thoko Didiza. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Agriculture, Land Reform, and Rural Development Thoko Didiza has called upon a higher power to strengthen and keep the families of those who lost their lives during an attack on a farm in Kestell in the Free State safe. Seven people were laid to rest on Saturday. READ: Kestell farm murder suspects abandon bail bid Didiza has also praised the people of Kestell. She says the small farming town is an example of a South Africa we should strive for, one with no racial divisions, no blurred lines, and where everyone is first and foremost human. Minister of Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development Thoko Didiza has called upon a higher power to strengthen and keep the families of those who lost their lives during an attack on a farm in Kestell in the Free State safe. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/NE8UvKyQ2O